How to install the wireless Xbox controllers for Windows.

http://support.xbox.com/en-US/xbox-on-other-devices/windows/xbox-controller-for-windows-setup

Downloading Drivers
1. Go to http://www.microsoft.com/hardware/en-us/downloads and click on
   'Gaming' > 'Xbox 360 Wireless Controller for Windows'
2. Download the correct drivers for your system
3. Run the downloaded installer


http://forums.xbox.com/xbox_forums/general_discussion/f/2196/t/135362.aspx
7th post

Using the Drivers
1. Go to Device Manager
2. Double click on 'Other devices' > 'Unknown device'
3. Click the 'Driver' tab
4. Click 'Update Driver...'
5. Choose 'Browse my computer for driver software'
6. Choose 'Let me pick from a list of device drivers on my computer'
7. Choose 'Microsoft Common Controller for Windows Class'
8. Choose 'Xbox 360 Wireless Receiver for Windows'
9. Ignore the warning and proceed anyway
10. ???
11. Profit
